  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study was to evaluate the lymphocyte phenotype in primary open- angle
      glaucoma (POAG) patients compared to healthy subjects of the same age, in order to confirm
      the importance of immune responses in glaucoma and the possible correlation to the severity
      of the disease.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
